- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper discusses both anonymization and de-anonymization techniques in the Bitcoin system, which are related to cryptography and security.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper discusses the Bitcoin protocol and network, which are related to networking and internet architecture.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper mentions clustering Bitcoin addresses, which involves data structures and algorithms.
- cs.DB (Databases) is another possible category as the paper discusses mapping Bitcoin addresses to users' identifications, which involves database techniques.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the privacy implications of the Bitcoin system and proposes directions for further research, which are related to the societal impact of the technology.
